(42, 7, 16, 2, 4, 31, 31, 'God hath visited his people', 'Divine Visitations and Response', 'This connection highlights the theme of God visiting His people, as seen in both passages. In Luke, the people recognize that ''God hath visited his people,'' paralleling the acknowledgment in Exodus that ''the Lord had visited the children of Israel.''', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
