(42, 7, 17, 40, 9, 26, 26, NULL, 'Connection of Fame and Rumor', 'Both passages emphasize the spread of news about Jesus, highlighting how his actions garnered widespread attention. The use of similar phrases indicates a thematic link regarding the impact of his ministry.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 17, 41, 1, 28, 28, 'throughout all the region round about', 'Spread of Fame', 'Both passages emphasize the spreading fame of Jesus throughout the regions. The phrase ''spread abroad throughout all the region round about'' in Mark parallels the ''rumour of him went forth throughout all Judea'' in Luke, highlighting the impact of his ministry.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 17, 41, 6, 14, 14, 'this rumour of him went forth', 'Spread of Jesus'' Reputation', 'This connection highlights the spread of Jesus'' fame in Judea, as noted in both passages. Luke 7:17 mentions that ''this rumour of him went forth,'' which aligns with Mark 6:14''s reference to ''his name was spread abroad.''', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 17, 42, 7, 14, 14, 'this rumour of him went forth', 'Rumor of Resurrection', 'This connection highlights the impact of Jesus'' miracle of raising the young man, which likely contributed to the widespread rumor about him throughout Judea. Both passages emphasize the significance of Jesus'' actions in drawing attention to his ministry.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 18, 43, 3, 26, 26, 'disciples of John', 'Disciples'' Reports on Jesus', 'This connection highlights the role of John''s disciples in both passages. In Luke, they report to John about Jesus'' activities, while in John, they express concern about Jesus'' growing following, indicating a shared narrative focus on the relationship between John and Jesus.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 18, 40, 11, 2, 19, 'the disciples of John', 'Connection Between John and Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize John''s inquiry about Jesus'' identity and the confirmation of Jesus'' works. The mention of John''s disciples in Luke leads directly to John''s question in Matthew, highlighting the relationship between their ministries.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 19, 23, 9, 6, 7, 'Art thou he that should come?', 'Expectation of the Messiah', 'This connection highlights the inquiry of John the Baptist about Jesus'' identity as the awaited one, paralleling the prophetic declaration in Isaiah about the coming child who will govern. Both passages emphasize the anticipation of a significant figure who will fulfill God''s promise of peace and justice.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
